Key Match Events: Evidence Makgopa scored the match-winning goal in the 57th minute
Teboho Mokoena scored a late free kick in the 5th minute of stoppage time
Post-Match Reflections: Walid Regragui, Morocco coach, took full responsibility for the loss
Miscellaneous Highlights: South Africa's victory marked an end to Morocco's continental curse as they remain without a Cup of Nations title since 1976
Others: Sofyan Amrabat was sent off late in the game for a professional foul
Morocco missed a penalty in the match
